{"questionId":"6005","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>To determine the acceleration due to gravity, a small metal sphere is dropped from rest and&nbsp;the time it takes to fall through a known distance and open a trapdoor is measured.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4747/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_15.43.42.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/01\"></p>\n<p>The following data are available.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {{\\text{Diameter of metal sphere}}}&amp;{ = 12.0 \\pm 0.1{\\text{ mm}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Distance between the point of release and the trapdoor}}}&amp;{ = 654 \\pm 2{\\text{ mm}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Measured time for fall}}}&amp;{ = 0.363 \\pm 0.002{\\text{ s}}} \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable columnalign=\"left\" rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Diameter of metal sphere</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>12.0</mn>\n          <mo>±</mo>\n          <mn>0.1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mm</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Distance between the point of release and the trapdoor</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>654</mn>\n          <mo>±</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mm</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Measured time for fall</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>0.363</mn>\n          <mo>±</mo>\n          <mn>0.002</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;s</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Using the following equation</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"{\\text{acceleration due to gravity}} = \\frac{{2 \\times {\\text{distance fallen by centre of mass of sphere}}}}{{{{{\\text{(measured time to fall)}}}^{\\text{2}}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>acceleration due to gravity</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>distance fallen by centre of mass of sphere</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>(measured time to fall)</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>2</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>calculate, for these data, the acceleration due to gravity including an estimate of&nbsp;the absolute uncertainty in your answer.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong><em>a</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2s}}{{{t^2}}} = \\frac{{2 \\times 0.642}}{{{{0.363}^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.642</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>0.363</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong>&nbsp;= 9.744&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>ms<sup>–2</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>fractional uncertainty in distance = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{2}{{642}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>642</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> <em><strong>AND</strong></em> fractional uncertainty in time = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.002}}{{0.363}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.002</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.363</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>total fractional uncertainty = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\Delta s}}{s} + 2\\frac{{\\Delta t}}{t}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>s</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>= 0.00311 + 2&nbsp;×&nbsp;0.00551<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>total absolute uncertainty = 0.1 <em><strong>or</strong></em> 0.14 <em><strong>AND</strong></em> same number of decimal places in value and uncertainty, <em>ie</em>: 9.7 ± 0.1 <strong><em>or </em></strong>9.74 ± 0.14</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept working in %</em>&nbsp;<em>for MP2 and MP3</em></p>\n<p><em>Final uncertainty must be the absolute uncertainty</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6005","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.1b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Using the following equation acceleration due to gravity = 2 × distance fallen by centre of mass of sphere (measured time to fall) 2 calculate, for these data, the acceleration due","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}